!! Understanding profiles

A //profile// is a small JSON document that tells JSON Convert how to turn your source JSON into TiddlyWiki tiddlers.  It does two things, and only two things:

* Picks which parts of the source become individual tiddlers (the ''records'').
* Describes, for each record, what the resulting tiddler's fields should look like (the ''bindings'').

That's the whole concept.  The rest of this guide is detail.

This is the canonical reference for profiles.  If you want a faster start, the [[Plug-in page|https://crosseye.github.io//TW5-JSON_Convert/#JSON%20Convert%20Console]] ships with sample profiles you can open in the editor and learn from.  When you want depth -- what `..` means in a binding, why your custom transform isn't showing in the picker, what `binding-token-star` means -- come back here.

